data.name: Developer
data.description: With access to push code to Github repos

threats.title: Only allow developer with correct access to push commits
threats.mitigation: Set up roles as needed, following "least privilege" rule. Set an expiry date for access.

threats.title: Pull requests (PRs) do not require approval.
threats.description:
Unapproved or unaudited changes are merged to codebase which becomes difficult to track down who made the change or who approve it. 

The unapproved or unaudited changes may also contain malicious or accidental changes which will lead to potential security risks.
threats.mitigation:
Always requesting PR approval for any changes to the codebase. When necessary, request multiple approvals.

Setup 'protected' branches which can force PR approval.

threats.title: Sensitive information is included in the connection to SonarCube instance
threats.description:
If access to SonarQube isn’t adequately secured, sensitive information like code vulnerabilities, internal architecture details, or proprietary code could be exposed to unauthorized users.

Public access to SonarQube reports can reveal specific weaknesses in your codebase, which attackers could exploit.
threats.mitigation:
Restrict access to SonarQube by configuring strong access controls. Limit user access to only those who need it, using Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) to assign the minimum necessary privileges for each role.
Restrict Access to Sensitive Reports by regularly reviewing permissions for critical projects to ensure that sensitive information remains protected.

threats.title: Published image being altered
threats.description:
The image could be altered (intentionally or unintentionally) by unauthorized users if the repository permissions aren’t tightly controlled.

If the Docker image itself is not adequately secured, a malicious actor could potentially tamper with the contents of the image, leading to compromised deployments when others pull and use the image.
threats.mitigation:
Enable image signing and verification.
Restrict permissions for who can push or modify images in Docker Hub repositories.
